sentences: Ioana Cristina Goicea (born 6 November 1992 in Bucharest, Romania) is a Romanian-born violinist.
In 2015, together with pianist Andrei Banciu, she won Second Prize at the International Competition “Premio Trio di Trieste”.
In 2016 she participated in the Chamber Music Academy of the Heidelberger Frühling Music Festival.
In 2017 she was invited to the Hitzacker Festival and its Academy.
In 2018 she took part in the Verbier Festival Academy.
Ioana Cristina Goicea plays a G.B. Guadagnini Violin (Parma, 1761), on loan from the German Music Instrument Fund – Deutsche Stiftung Musikleben.
Her debut CD „Recital“ together with pianist Andrey Gugnin was released in early 2019 on New Zealand's Atoll Records Label.
